{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"situational-15000","unitId":"scene-367","title":"地震海啸","sectionId":"chapter-16","sectionTitle":"天文地理有规律","pageStart":1790,"pageEnd":1794,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":18,"duplicateEntryCount":22,"pages":[{"number":1790,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"367 地震海啸"},{"type":"section","text":"Step1 场景词"},{"type":"entry","text":"earthquake monitoring地震监控","headword":"earthquake monitoring"},{"type":"entry","text":"seismological [ˌsaɪzməˈlɒdʒɪkl]","headword":"seismological"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.地震学上的"},{"type":"note","text":"◎Seismological Bureau地震局"},{"type":"entry","text":"seismographer [ˈsaɪzməɡrɑːfə(r)]","headword":"seismographer"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.地震学家"},{"type":"entry","text":"seismometre [saɪzˈmɒmɪtə(r)]","headword":"seismometre"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.地震检波器"}]},{"number":1791,"blocks":[{"type":"note","text":"◎marine seismometre海洋地震表"},{"type":"entry","text":"seismic belt 地震带","headword":"seismic belt"},{"type":"entry","text":"earthquake zone 地震带","headword":"earthquake zone"},{"type":"entry","text":"Richter scale 里氏震级","headword":"Richter scale"},{"type":"entry","text":"hypocentre [ˈhaɪpəʊsentə(r)]","headword":"hypocentre"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.震源"},{"type":"note","text":"◎hypocentre parametre震源参数"},{"type":"entry","text":"seismic wave 震波","headword":"seismic wave"},{"type":"entry","text":"epicentre [ˈepɪsentə(r)]","headword":"epicentre"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.震中"},{"type":"note","text":"◎epicentre distribution震中分布"},{"type":"entry","text":"aseismatic [eɪsaɪzˈmætɪk]","headword":"aseismatic"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.抗震的"},{"type":"note","text":"◎aseismatic measure抗震措施"}]},{"number":1792,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"plate boundary板块交界处","headword":"plate boundary"},{"type":"entry","text":"roll across 波动，起伏，横摇","headword":"roll across"},{"type":"entry","text":"rip through 裂开，破开","headword":"rip through"}]},{"number":1793,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"tsunami warning system 海啸预警系统","headword":"tsunami warning system"},{"type":"entry","text":"sea wave 海浪","headword":"sea wave"}]},{"number":1794,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"high sea 大浪","headword":"high sea"},{"type":"entry","text":"monster wave 狂浪","headword":"monster wave"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"},{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 1"},{"type":"example","text":"A：Today, let's talk something about the earthquake. （今天我们来讨"},{"type":"text","text":"论有关地震的话题。）"},{"type":"example","text":"B：It is a sorrowful topic. It brings me to remember the Sichuan"},{"type":"text","text":"earthquake. （这是个悲伤的话题，让我想起了四川地震。）"},{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 2"},{"type":"example","text":"A：China is located on the Eurasia plate, where earthquakes happen"},{"type":"text","text":"frequently due to the earth's plates knocking against each other. （中国地"},{"type":"text","text":"处亚欧板块，这是板块容易互相撞击的地区，因此地震活动频繁。）"},{"type":"example","text":"B：China does have been plagued by numerous destructive"},{"type":"text","text":"earthquakes during its long history. （在悠久的历史中，中国的确遭受了"},{"type":"text","text":"许多破坏性的大地震。）"}]}]}